  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sleep disordered breathing is common in patients with chronic heart failure. Adaptive
      servoventilation is a novel method of treatment central sleep apnoea, especially associated
      with Cheyne-Stokes-respiration. The aim of the study is to investigate effect of adaptive
      servoventilation on cardiac function, exercise tolerance and quality of life in patients with
      chronic heart failure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
